text: Ödön Toldi (17 June 1893 - 26 January 1966) was a Hungarian swimmer. He competed in the men's 200 metre breaststroke event at the 1908 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1893 births Category:1966 deaths Category:Hungarian male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Hungary Category:Swimmers at the 1908 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Budapest
